Background: Majoring in biology… A member of The Washington Post First-Team All-Metro squad from in 2011 when he amassed 12 goals and 19 assists… Also earned All-State honors in his senior season, helping the Bulldogs to a state title… Selected to Prince George’s county First Team in both 2010 and 2011… Scored two goals and added an assist vs. Severna Park in the state semifinal contest before his side defeated a previously-unbeaten Walter Johnson squad in the title game played at UMBC… A member of the National Honor Society…,Also has competed for the two-time Virginia state champion Annandale Knights FC… Lists favorite movie as Invincible and favorite professional team as Manchster United… Considering a career in physical therapy… Has an older sister, Erica, who is 22, and a younger brother, Brendan, age 17… Son of Robin and Eric LeMaster… Born Sept. 11, 1994.
